Heat oven to 425 degrees F. Cook and stir onion in margarine in 2-quart saucepan until tender. Stir in flour. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly. Remove from heat; stir in milk. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute. Stir in remaining ingredients except Fillets. Place Fillets, with sides touching, in ungreased rectangular baking dish, 11x7 inch; pour sauce over Fillets. Bake uncovered until hot, 25 to 30 minutes.